Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: The station boys were all assembled to welcome us on our return, and doubtless also to draw their own conclusions as to how we had come through the ordeal of a two-hours' gallop. But they treated us real well, and after a cup of tea and some tip-top station mutton we reluctantly bade them farewell and turned for home just at six o'clock, arriving in Hawera at eleven.
